#lg G	sa-jara


@(33-52=c2553.G.33) In the overflowing of his heart, @wDN{An} has chosen him as king and blessed the royal descendant: @q{“@wRN{Lipit-@wDN{Eštar}}, on whom I bestowed power, may you lift your head high! May you spread fearsome radiance as if you were the front of a rising tempest! May your storm cover the enemy territories, the disobedient countries! You have established justice in @wGN{Sumer} and @wGN{Akkad}, and made the Land feel content. @wRN{Lipit-@wDN{Eštar}}, son of @wDN{Enlil}, may you shine as brilliantly as the sunlight! May concord be created under you in the established cities, settlements and dwellings! May the black-headed people, numerous as flocks, follow the right path under you! @wRN{Lipit-@wDN{Eštar}}, even in far-away foreign countries, you will be the king! @wDN{Enlil} has faithfully bestowed on you the princely august throne, the eternal ornament of kingship; he has made it firm for you. May you never cease to wear the crown that @wDN{Suen} has placed firmly on your head! @wDN{Enki} has adorned you with princely divine powers. @wDN{Inana} escorts (?) you with the garment of princeship. The friendly guardians and the protecting genii of the @wTN{E-kur} stand by you. May the food offerings, wine, and milk that you bring ……! Son and creature of @wDN{Enlil}, may everything be pleasant for you!”}

$ (2 lines missing)

